properties.name: id
properties.description: The unique ID of the CellStyle.

properties.name: isValid
properties.description: Returns true if the object specifier resolves to valid objects.

properties.name: parent
properties.description: The parent of the CellStyle (a Document, Application or CellStyleGroup).

properties.name: index
properties.description: The index of the CellStyle within its containing object.

properties.name: events
properties.description: A collection of events.

properties.name: eventListeners
properties.description: A collection of event listeners.

properties.name: graphicLeftInset
properties.description: The left inset of the graphic cell. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: graphicTopInset
properties.description: The top inset of the graphic cell. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: graphicRightInset
properties.description: The right inset of the graphic cell. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: graphicBottomInset
properties.description: The bottom inset of the graphic cell. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: clipContentToGraphicCell
properties.description: If true, clips the graphic cell's content to width and height of the cell. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: textTopInset
properties.description: The top inset of the text cell. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: textLeftInset
properties.description: The left inset of the text cell. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: textBottomInset
properties.description: The bottom inset of the text cell. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: textRightInset
properties.description: The right inset of the text cell. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: clipContentToTextCell
properties.description: If true, clips the text cell's content to width and height of the cell. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: basedOn
properties.description: The style that this style is based on. Can return: CellStyle or String.

properties.name: appliedParagraphStyle
properties.description: The paragraph style applied to the text. Can return: ParagraphStyle or NothingEnum enumerator. Can also accept: String.

properties.name: gradientFillLength
properties.description: The length (of a linear gradient) or radius (of a radial gradient) applied to the fill of the object. Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: gradientFillAngle
properties.description: The angle of a linear gradient applied to the fill of the object. (Range: -180 to 180). Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: gradientFillStart
properties.description: The starting point (in page coordinates) of a gradient applied to the fill of the CellStyle, in the format [x, y]. Can return: Array of 2 Units or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: topInset
properties.description: The top inset of the cell. The API has been deprecated. Use TextTopInset or GraphicTopInset. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: leftInset
properties.description: The left inset of the cell.The API has been deprecated. Use TextLeftInset or GraphicLeftInset. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: bottomInset
properties.description: The bottom inset of the cell.The API has been deprecated. Use TextBottomInset or GraphicBottomInset. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: rightInset
properties.description: The right inset of the cell.The API has been deprecated. Use TextLeftInset or GraphicRightInset. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: fillColor
properties.description: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the fill of the object. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator. Can also accept: String.

properties.name: fillTint
properties.description: The tint (as a percentage) of the fill of the object. Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: overprintFill
properties.description: If true, the fill of the object will overprint. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: topLeftDiagonalLine
properties.description: If true, draws a diagonal line starting from the top left. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: topRightDiagonalLine
properties.description: If true, draws a diagonal line starting from the top right. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: diagonalLineInFront
properties.description: If true, draws the diagonal line in front of cell contents. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: diagonalLineStrokeWeight
properties.description: The diagonal line stroke weight. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: diagonalLineStrokeType
properties.description: The stroke type of the diagonal line(s). Can return: StrokeStyle or NothingEnum enumerator. Can also accept: String.

properties.name: diagonalLineStrokeColor
properties.description: The diagonal line color, specified as a swatch. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: diagonalLineStrokeTint
properties.description: The diagonal line tint (as a percentage). (Range: 0 to 100). Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: diagonalLineStrokeOverprint
properties.description: If true, the diagonal line stroke will overprint. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: diagonalLineStrokeGapColor
properties.description: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the gap of the diagonal line stroke. Note: Not valid when diagonal line stroke type is solid. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: diagonalLineStrokeGapTint
properties.description: The tint (as a percentage) of the diagonal line stroke gap color. Note: Not valid when diagonal line stroke type is solid. Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: diagonalLineStrokeGapOverprint
properties.description: If true, the stroke gap of the diagonal line will overprint. Note: Not valid when diagonal line stroke type is solid. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: clipContentToCell
properties.description: If true, clips the cell's content to width and height of the cell. The API has been deprecated. Use ClipContentsToTextCell or ClipContentsToPageItemCell. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: firstBaselineOffset
properties.description: The distance between the baseline of the text and the top inset of the cell. Can return: FirstBaseline enumerator or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: verticalJustification
properties.description: The vertical alignment of cell. Can return: VerticalJustification enumerator or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: paragraphSpacingLimit
properties.description: The maximum space that can be added between paragraphs in a cell. Note: Valid only when vertical justification is justified. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: minimumFirstBaselineOffset
properties.description: The space between the baseline of the text and the top inset of the frame or cell. Can return: Unit (0 - 8640 points) or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: rotationAngle
properties.description: The rotation angle (in degrees) of the cell, specified as one of the following values: 0, 90, 180, or 270. Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: leftEdgeStrokeWeight
properties.description: The stroke weight of the left edge border stroke. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: leftEdgeStrokeType
properties.description: The stroke type of the left edge. Can return: StrokeStyle or NothingEnum enumerator. Can also accept: String.

properties.name: leftEdgeStrokeColor
properties.description: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the left edge border stroke. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: leftEdgeStrokeTint
properties.description: The tint (as a percentage) of the left edge border stroke. (Range: 0 to 100). Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: leftEdgeStrokeOverprint
properties.description: If true, the left edge border stroke will overprint. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: leftEdgeStrokeGapColor
properties.description: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the gap of the left edge border stroke. Note: Not valid when left edge stroke type is solid. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: leftEdgeStrokeGapTint
properties.description: The tint (as a percentage) of the left edge border stroke gap color. (Range: 0 to 100) Note: Not valid when left edge stroke type is solid. Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: leftEdgeStrokeGapOverprint
properties.description: If true, the gap color of the left edge border stroke will overprint. Note: Not valid when left edge stroke type is solid. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: topEdgeStrokeWeight
properties.description: The stroke weight of the top edge border stroke. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: topEdgeStrokeType
properties.description: The stroke type of the top edge. Can return: StrokeStyle or NothingEnum enumerator. Can also accept: String.

properties.name: topEdgeStrokeColor
properties.description: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the top edge border stroke. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: topEdgeStrokeTint
properties.description: The tint (as a percentage) of the top edge border stroke. (Range: 0 to 100). Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: topEdgeStrokeOverprint
properties.description: If true, the top edge border stroke will overprint. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: topEdgeStrokeGapColor
properties.description: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the gap of the top edge border stroke. Note: Not valid when top edge stroke type is solid. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: topEdgeStrokeGapTint
properties.description: The tint (as a percentage) of the top edge border stroke gap color. (Range: 0 to 100) Note: Not valid when top edge stroke type is solid. Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: topEdgeStrokeGapOverprint
properties.description: If true, the gap color of the top edge border stroke will overprint. Note: Not valid when top edge stroke type is solid. . Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: rightEdgeStrokeWeight
properties.description: The stroke weight of the right edge border stroke. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: rightEdgeStrokeType
properties.description: The stroke type of the right edge. Can return: StrokeStyle or NothingEnum enumerator. Can also accept: String.

properties.name: rightEdgeStrokeColor
properties.description: The color, specified as a swatch, of the right edge border stroke. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: rightEdgeStrokeTint
properties.description: The tint (as a percentage) of the right edge border stroke. (Range: 0 to 100). Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: rightEdgeStrokeOverprint
properties.description: If true, the right edge border stroke will overprint. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: rightEdgeStrokeGapColor
properties.description: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the gap of the right edge border stroke. Note: Not valid when right edge stroke type is solid. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: rightEdgeStrokeGapTint
properties.description: The tint (as a percentage) of the right edge border stroke gap color. (Range: 0 to 100) Note: Not valid when right edge stroke type is solid. Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: rightEdgeStrokeGapOverprint
properties.description: If true, the gap color of the right edge border stroke will overprint. Note: Not valid when right edge stroke type is solid. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: bottomEdgeStrokeWeight
properties.description: The stroke weight of the bottom edge border stroke. Can return: Unit or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: bottomEdgeStrokeType
properties.description: The stroke type of the bottom edge. Can return: StrokeStyle or NothingEnum enumerator. Can also accept: String.

properties.name: bottomEdgeStrokeColor
properties.description: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the bottom edge border stroke. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: bottomEdgeStrokeTint
properties.description: The tint (as a percentage) of the bottom edge border stroke. Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: bottomEdgeStrokeOverprint
properties.description: If true, the bottom edge border stroke will overprint. Can return: Boolean or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: bottomEdgeStrokeGapColor
properties.description: The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the gap of the bottom edge border stroke. Note: Not valid when bottom edge stroke type is solid. Can return: Swatch or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.description: The tint (as a percentage) of the bottom edge border stroke gap color. (Range: 0 to 100) Note: Not valid when bottom edge stroke type is solid. Can return: Real or NothingEnum enumerator.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the style.

properties.name: label
properties.description: A property that can be set to any string.

properties.name: properties
properties.description: A property that allows setting of several properties at the same time.

parameters.name: replacingWith
parameters.description: The style to apply in place of the deleted style. (Optional)

methods.name: move

parameters.name: to
parameters.description: The location relative to the reference object or within the containing object.

parameters.name: reference
parameters.description: The reference object. Note: Required when the to parameter specifies before or after. Can accept: ParagraphStyle, ParagraphStyleGroup, CharacterStyle, CharacterStyleGroup, CellStyle, CellStyleGroup, TableStyle, TableStyleGroup, Document or Application. (Optional)

methods.description: Moves the style to the specified location.

methods.name: insertLabel
methods.description: Sets the label to the value associated with the specified key.

methods.name: extractLabel
methods.description: Gets the label value associated with the specified key.

methods.name: toSource
methods.description: Generates a string which, if executed, will return the CellStyle.

methods.name: getElements
methods.description: Resolves the object specifier, creating an array of object references.

parameters.name: handler
parameters.description: The event handler. Can accept: File or JavaScript Function.

parameters.name: handler
parameters.description: The registered event handler. Can accept: File or JavaScript Function.
